30/**
31* <p>Represents a polynomial whose coefficients are elements of a GF.
32* Instances of this class are immutable.</p>
33*
34* <p>Much credit is due to William Rucklidge since portions of this code are an indirect
35* port of his C++ Reed-Solomon implementation.</p>
36*
37* @author Sean Owen
38*/
39class GenericGFPoly
40{
41 struct Coefficients : public std::vector<int>
42 {
43 void reserve(size_t s)
44 {
45 if (capacity() < s)
46 std::vector<int>::reserve(std::max(size_t(32), s));
47 }
48
49 void resize(size_t s)
50 {
51 reserve(s);
52 std::vector<int>::resize(s);
53 }
54
55 void resize(size_t s, int i)
56 {
57 reserve(s);
58 std::vector<int>::resize(s, i);
59 }
60 };
61
62public:
63 // Build a invalid object, so that this can be used in container or return by reference,
64 // any access to invalid object is undefined behavior.
65 GenericGFPoly() = default;
66
67 /**
68 * @param field the {@link GenericGF} instance representing the field to use
69 * to perform computations
70 * @param coefficients coefficients as ints representing elements of GF(size), arranged
71 * from most significant (highest-power term) coefficient to least significant
72 * @throws IllegalArgumentException if argument is null or empty,
73 * or if leading coefficient is 0 and this is not a
74 * constant polynomial (that is, it is not the monomial "0").
75 */
76 GenericGFPoly(const GenericGF& field, std::vector<int>&& coefficients) : _field(&field)
77 {
78 assert(!coefficients.empty());
79 _coefficients.swap(coefficients); // _coefficients = coefficients
80 normalize();
81 }
82 GenericGFPoly(const GenericGF& field, const std::vector<int>& coefficients) : GenericGFPoly(field, std::vector<int>(coefficients)) {}
83
84 GenericGFPoly& operator=(GenericGFPoly&& other) = default;
85 GenericGFPoly(GenericGFPoly&& other) = default;
86
87 GenericGFPoly& operator=(const GenericGFPoly& other) {
88 assert(_field == other._field);
89 _coefficients.reserve(other._coefficients.size());
90 _coefficients = other._coefficients;
91 return *this;
92 }
93
94 GenericGFPoly(const GenericGFPoly& other) {
95 _field = other._field;
96 *this = other;
97 }
98
99 const std::vector<int>& coefficients() const {
100 return _coefficients;
101 }
102
103 /**
104 * @return degree of this polynomial
105 */
106 int degree() const {
107 return Size(_coefficients) - 1;
108 }
109
110 /**
111 * @return true iff this polynomial is the monomial "0"
112 */
113 bool isZero() const {
114 return _coefficients[0] == 0;
115 }
116
117 /**
118 * @return coefficient of x^degree term in this polynomial
119 */
120 int coefficient(int degree) const {
121 return _coefficients[_coefficients.size() - 1 - degree];
122 }
123
124 /**
125 * @return evaluation of this polynomial at a given point
126 */
127 int evaluateAt(int a) const;
128
129 GenericGFPoly& addOrSubtract(GenericGFPoly& other);
130 GenericGFPoly& multiply(const GenericGFPoly& other);
131 GenericGFPoly& multiply(int scalar);
132 GenericGFPoly& multiplyByMonomial(int degree, int coefficient);
133 GenericGFPoly& divide(const GenericGFPoly& other, GenericGFPoly& quotient);
134
135 friend void swap(GenericGFPoly& a, GenericGFPoly& b)
136 {
137 std::swap(a._field, b._field);
138 std::swap(a._coefficients, b._coefficients);
139 }
140
141private:
142 friend class GenericGF;
143
144 void normalize();
145
146 const GenericGF* _field = nullptr;
147 Coefficients _coefficients, _cache; // _cache is used for malloc caching
148};
